service: This is the AWS HealthOmics API Reference. For an introduction to the service, see What is AWS HealthOmics? in the AWS HealthOmics User Guide.

operations.CompleteMultipartReadSetUpload: Concludes a multipart upload once you have uploaded all the components.
operations.CreateAnnotationStoreVersion: Creates a new version of an annotation store.
operations.CreateShare:
Creates a cross-account shared resource. The resource owner makes an offer to share the resource with the principal subscriber (an AWS user with a different account than the resource owner).

The following resources support cross-account sharing:

  • Healthomics variant stores

  • Healthomics annotation stores

  • Private workflows
operations.DeleteAnnotationStoreVersions: Deletes one or multiple versions of an annotation store.
operations.DeleteShare: Deletes a resource share. If you are the resource owner, the subscriber will no longer have access to the shared resource. If you are the subscriber, this operation deletes your access to the share.
operations.GetAnnotationImportJob: Gets information about an annotation import job.
operations.GetAnnotationStoreVersion: Retrieves the metadata for an annotation store version.
operations.GetReadSet: Gets a file from a read set.
operations.GetReadSetActivationJob: Gets information about a read set activation job.
operations.GetReadSetExportJob: Gets information about a read set export job.
operations.GetReadSetImportJob: Gets information about a read set import job.
operations.GetReferenceImportJob: Gets information about a reference import job.
operations.GetReferenceMetadata: Gets information about a genome reference's metadata.
operations.GetRun:
Gets information about a workflow run.

If a workflow is shared with you, you cannot export information about the run.
operations.GetRunGroup: Gets information about a workflow run group.
operations.GetRunTask: Gets information about a workflow run task.
operations.GetShare: Retrieves the metadata for the specified resource share.
operations.GetVariantImportJob: Gets information about a variant import job.
operations.GetWorkflow:
Gets information about a workflow.

If a workflow is shared with you, you cannot export the workflow.
operations.ListAnnotationImportJobs: Retrieves a list of annotation import jobs.
operations.ListAnnotationStoreVersions: Lists the versions of an annotation store.
operations.ListMultipartReadSetUploads: Lists multipart read set uploads and for in progress uploads. Once the upload is completed, a read set is created and the upload will no longer be returned in the response.
operations.ListReadSetActivationJobs: Retrieves a list of read set activation jobs.
operations.ListReadSetExportJobs: Retrieves a list of read set export jobs.
operations.ListReadSetImportJobs: Retrieves a list of read set import jobs.
operations.ListReadSetUploadParts: This operation will list all parts in a requested multipart upload for a sequence store.
operations.ListReferenceImportJobs: Retrieves a list of reference import jobs.
operations.ListRunTasks: Retrieves a list of tasks for a run.
operations.ListShares: Retrieves the resource shares associated with an account. Use the filter parameter to retrieve a specific subset of the shares.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Retrieves a list of tags for a resource.
operations.ListVariantImportJobs: Retrieves a list of variant import jobs.
operations.StartReadSetActivationJob: Activates an archived read set. To reduce storage charges, Amazon Omics archives unused read sets after 30 days.
operations.StartReadSetExportJob: Exports a read set to Amazon S3.
operations.StartRun:
Starts a workflow run. To duplicate a run, specify the run's ID and a role ARN. The remaining parameters are copied from the previous run.

StartRun will not support re-run for a workflow that is shared with you.

The total number of runs in your account is subject to a quota per Region. To avoid needing to delete runs manually, you can set the retention mode to REMOVE. Runs with this setting are deleted automatically when the run quoata is exceeded.

By default, the run uses STATIC storage. For STATIC storage, set the storageCapacity field. You can set the storage type to DYNAMIC. You do not set storageCapacity, because HealthOmics dynamically scales the storage up or down as required. For more information about static and dynamic storage, see Running workflows in the AWS HealthOmics User Guide.
operations.UpdateAnnotationStoreVersion: Updates the description of an annotation store version.
operations.UploadReadSetPart: This operation uploads a specific part of a read set. If you upload a new part using a previously used part number, the previously uploaded part will be overwritten.
